title: National Capital Parks-East: Archive
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     News     News Releases     Archive                Archive           Subscribe  | What is RSS     May 11, 2015  Public Comments on Invasive Plant Management Plan  The National Park Service (NPS) is accepting public scoping comments on an Invasive Plant Management Plan and Environmental Assessment (plan/EA) for 15 national parks in the greater Washington DC region.   September 24, 2014  Gopaul Noojibail Named Superintendent  Responsibility includes Frederick Douglass, Mary McLeod Bethune Council House and Carter G. Woodson Home national historic sites, Anacostia Park, Kenilworth Park and Aquatic Gardens, Capitol Hill parks.
